.TH simple_shell 1 "" "Holberton School" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
simple_shell \- simple UNIX command interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a small shell that reads a line from standard input, parses it into a command and its arguments, and executes it. 
In interactive mode it displays a prompt and waits for user input; in non\-interactive mode it reads and executes commands until EOF. 

.SH BUILTINS
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell with an optional status.
.TP
.B env
Print the current environment. 

.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns the status of the last executed command, or a non\-zero value on error. 

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sh (1),
.BR bash (1)
